## Task workflow & system rules

Tasks move through exactly four statuses: **`inbox` → `in_progress` → `review` → `done`**.

1. **Always check `status` first.** Before doing any work on a task, read its current
   `status`. If it is `inbox` and you are going to work on it, PATCH `status=in_progress`
   FIRST (with a short `status_reason`). Never work on a task that is still `inbox` — the
   board must reflect reality.
2. **`output` is mandatory for `review` and `done`.** The `output` field is the ONLY
   deliverable a human can read in Mission Control. Files you create on local disk are
   temporary and invisible to the user. A PATCH to `review` or `done` with an empty
   `output` is rejected with **409 `task_output_required`**. Put the real result
   (summary + links/paths/values) in `output`, not "done, see local file".
3. **`status_reason`** — include a short reason whenever you change `status` so the
   timeline is readable.
4. **`review` means "waiting for the lead".** When you move a task to `review` it is no
   longer assigned to you; the lead reviews it and either moves it to `done` or sends it
   back. Do not mark your own task `done` unless you are the lead and all gates pass.
5. **Gates before `done`** (any may be enabled per project): a linked approval must be
   approved (`require_approval_for_done`); the task must come from `review`
   (`require_review_before_done`); all blocking dependency tasks must be `done`; required
   custom fields filled. Violations return **409**.
6. **Who can change status:** if `only_lead_can_change_status` is on, workers cannot move
   tasks — ask the lead. A worker may only edit `status`, `output`, `comment`, and custom
   fields (not title/description/priority/assignee).
7. **Post progress as task comments**, not chat. Keep them high-signal (artifact /
   decision / blocker / handoff).

## Error handling

- `401` → token is stale; **re-read** `mission_control_credential.json` and retry once. Do not reuse the old shell variable.
- `403` → you are authenticated but not authorized; ask the lead/user for permission. Never try to widen scope.
- `409` → a rule blocked the change. Common cause: moving to `review`/`done` with an empty
  `output` (`task_output_required`) — fill `output` and retry. Other 409s: pending/approved
  approval required, blocked by dependencies, or review-before-done. Read the `detail.message`.
- `422` → payload schema mismatch; open `/tmp/openapi.json` and inspect `components.schemas.<Name>` for the request body. Fix and retry.
- `5xx`/network → do **not** write memory or task updates this cycle. Retry next heartbeat.

## When you are stuck

Ask one clarifying question instead of guessing field names or paths. If you need an endpoint that is not in `references/api_schema.md` or the OpenAPI doc filtered to `{{ role_tag }}`, that endpoint is **not** for your role.
